It's clear you're doing _something_ but nobody in the community knows *what*.  It'd be nice if there was some visibility into where  this is going and what is trying to be accomplished.

Removed reference to Redfish CSDL... it was added inadvertently.

The intention is to identify each section's type uniquely, even in the absence of the section-descriptor.
Now we've lost all of the "why".  Why should a maintainer take this change?

> The intention is to identify each section's type uniquely, even in the absence of the section-descriptor.

Put this in the description.  We're trying to get unique type names in json schema for handling conversion failures.  Add that to your commit message please.
Already done (with example)
